{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC18","role":"sampleCode","title":"What’s New in Cocoa for macOS"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Gain insights into the latest in Cocoa frameworks for macOS. Hear about Dark Mode, control tinting, contextual workflows for Touch Bar and Finder, and other improvements in AppKit, Foundation, and related areas. Get an overview and guide to the sessions that we have this year covering advancements in Cocoa."}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc18\/209","type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (40 min)"}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-209-whats-new-in-cocoa-for-macos"]}],"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-209-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-for-macOS","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2},{"type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-210-Introducing-Dark-Mode","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-218-Advanced-Dark-Mode","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-221-TextKit-Best-Practices","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-222-Data-You-Can-Trust","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-604-Metal-for-OpenGL-Developers"],"style":"list"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"WWDC18-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-Icon.png"}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC18-Icon.png","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-218-Advanced-Dark-Mode":{"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Advanced Dark Mode","abstract":[{"text":"Step deeper into Dark Mode adoption in your macOS application. Learn about the powerful Cocoa technologies at the core of Dark Mode, and take a detailed look at the APIs and best practices for adapting to this beautiful new look.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-218-advanced-dark-mode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-218-Advanced-Dark-Mode","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc18/209":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc18\/209","type":"download","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc18\/209"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18":{"title":"WWDC18","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 10, Swift 4.2, iOS 12, macOS 10.14 (Mojave), tvOS 12, watchOS 5."}],"kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC18-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","type":"card"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"type":"link","title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-221-TextKit-Best-Practices":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-221-textkit-best-practices","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Leverage the abilities of TextKit to provide the best experience possible displaying and editing text. Get the best performance out of your app by using TextKit effectively. Learn the concepts to do more complex handling, layout and presentation."}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-221-TextKit-Best-Practices","role":"sampleCode","title":"TextKit Best Practices"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-210-Introducing-Dark-Mode":{"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Introducing Dark Mode","abstract":[{"text":"Hear from the Apple design team about the principles and concepts that anchor Dark Mode. Learn the basics of enhancing your app with this new appearance, and add an experience that people are sure to love.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-210-introducing-dark-mode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-210-Introducing-Dark-Mode","type":"topic"},"WWDC18.jpeg":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18.jpeg"}],"identifier":"WWDC18.jpeg","type":"image","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-604-Metal-for-OpenGL-Developers":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-604-metal-for-opengl-developers","type":"topic","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-604-Metal-for-OpenGL-Developers","abstract":[{"text":"Metal is the foundation for accelerated graphics and compute on Apple platforms, enabling your apps and games to tap into the incredible power of the GPU. Get introduced to essential Metal capabilities and understand the recommended approach for transitioning OpenGL-based apps onto the Metal API.","type":"text"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Metal for OpenGL Developers"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-222-Data-You-Can-Trust":{"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","title":"Data You Can Trust","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A lot can go wrong when loading data into your app. Whether you work directly with JSON and property lists, or with higher-level APIs such as NSCoding and Codable, learn how to defend your customers and secure your code against invalid or malicious data. Avoid fatal assumptions by validating payload structure, type information and domain correctness, to turn the data you work with into data you can trust."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-222-data-you-can-trust","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-222-Data-You-Can-Trust","type":"topic"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"image"}}}